race.comment: CUMBRIA RICH (8) has mixed form a little and missed the frame the last two but was a Grade 5 winner three back (20.80) at this track over 365m. This looks easier and expected to improve sharply. SEVEN INN (1) is an honest type who is new here. Had a squeeze draw but was too good last time scoring by 0.8 lengths at Wagga over 320m (18.66). Has a strong record out of this box with six wins and three minor placings from nine starts. Will go close again if runs up to latest. ZIPPING NEYMAR (3) can find the frame without surprising. Something for the Multiples: ZIP ZIPPITY ZIP (4)
